Newcastle host Arsenal in their Carabao Cup semi-final second leg at St James' Park with Eddie Howe's side boasting a two-goal lead.

The Toon beat the Gunners 2-0 in north London last month, with goals from Alexander Isak and Anthony Gordon giving Newcastle a strong advantage heading into the second leg.

Newcastle, who have lost two of their last three games after winning nine in a row in all competitions, are hoping to lift the Carabao Cup for the first time.

Article continues below advert

Howe's men booked their place in the final in 2023, though they ended up losing 2-0 against Manchester United at Wembley.

Watch Newcastle v Arsenal on Sky Sports
Arsenal have won the competition on two occasions, with their last success coming in 1993. They've reached the final three times since 2007, but the Gunners failed to get over the line.

Mikel Arteta's side come into the clash on the back of their 5-1 demolition of Manchester City at the Emirates on Sunday, and they'll be hoping for a repeat of that performance as they look to book their place in the final in March.

